The paper discusses Bayesian neural learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The use of surrogate-assisted optimization is also mentioned, which is a common technique in optimization and simulation-based modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
